main event: A civilian ground observer reported seeing a V-shaped, white and gray object in the sky near Webster Village, Maryland on April 3, 1953.
interesting points: The object was under observation for 36 minutes.
No vapor or exhaust trails were observed, and no estimated speed was provided.
No sounds or maneuvering were reported.
The sighting was made by a civilian ground observer volunteer named Patrick Lynch.
The weather conditions included cloudy skies, 2-mile visibility, and varying wind speeds and directions at different altitudes.
witnesses: civilian ground observer volunteer Patrick Lynch
